what is india's nation animal
ChatGPT
India's national animal is the Bengal Tiger (Panthera tigris tigris). It was declared the national animal of India in 1972 due to its cultural, ecological, and conservational significance. The Bengal Tiger is a symbol of strength, power, and grace and is an integral part of Indian folklore, history, and art. As a critically endangered species, efforts are being made to protect and conserve these majestic creatures to ensure their survival for future generations.

