You enjoy a mix of savory and slightly spicy flavors.
You'd like to avoid any dairy products in this recipe.
Based on your inputs, here's a personalized recipe for "Spicy Chicken Stir-Fry with Garlic Rice":

Ingredients:

2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts, thinly sliced
1 red bell pepper, sliced into strips
1 green bell pepper, sliced into strips
1 large onion, thinly sliced
4 cloves of garlic, minced
2 cups of cooked rice
3 tablespoons olive oil
Salt and pepper to taste
For the Stir-Fry Sauce:

3 tablespoons soy sauce (or tamari for gluten-free)
2 tablespoons sriracha sauce (adjust to your desired level of spiciness)
1 tablespoon honey (or maple syrup for a vegan option)
Instructions:

In a small bowl, mix together the ingredients for the stir-fry sauce: soy sauce, sriracha sauce, and honey. Set aside.

Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a frying pan or skillet over medium-high heat. Add the sliced chicken and cook until it's no longer pink, about 5-6 minutes. Remove the chicken from the pan and set aside.

In the same pan, add the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Add the minced garlic and sauté for about 30 seconds until fragrant.

Add the sliced onions and bell peppers to the pan. Stir-fry them for 3-4 minutes until they are slightly tender but still crisp.

Pour the prepared stir-fry sauce over the vegetables and toss everything together. Cook for an additional 2 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.

Add the cooked chicken back into the pan with the vegetables and sauce. Stir everything together and cook for another 1-2 minutes to heat the chicken through and coat it with the sauce.

Season the stir-fry with salt and pepper according to your taste.

Serve the spicy chicken stir-fry over a bed of garlic rice. To make the garlic rice, you can simply mix the cooked rice with a teaspoon of minced garlic and a pinch of salt.

Enjoy your flavorful and spicy chicken stir-fry with garlic rice, made with the ingredients you have on hand and cooked using your stove and frying pan/skillet!

Feel free to adjust the spiciness or add more vegetables if desired. Happy cooking!

