Thank you for the additional information. Since you prefer a vegan recipe and you have access to a stove, let's modify the previous recipe accordingly to create a delicious and vegan-friendly stir-fry.

Vegan Spicy Vegetable Stir-Fry with Garlic Rice:

Ingredients:

1 cup tofu, cubed (or substitute with tempeh or seitan for a different texture)
1 red bell pepper, sliced into strips
1 green bell pepper, sliced into strips
1 large onion, thinly sliced
2 tomatoes, diced
4 cloves of garlic, minced
2 cups of cooked rice
3 tablespoons vegetable oil (e.g., olive oil or sesame oil)
Salt and pepper to taste
For the Vegan Stir-Fry Sauce:

3 tablespoons soy sauce (or tamari for gluten-free)
2 tablespoons sriracha sauce (adjust to your desired level of spiciness)
1 tablespoon maple syrup (or agave nectar)
Instructions:

In a small bowl, mix together the ingredients for the vegan stir-fry sauce: soy sauce, sriracha sauce, and maple syrup. Set aside.

Heat 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil in a frying pan or skillet over medium-high heat. Add the cubed tofu (or your preferred vegan protein) and cook until it's lightly browned and slightly crispy, about 4-5 minutes. Remove the tofu from the pan and set aside.

In the same pan, add the remaining 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil. Add the minced garlic and sauté for about 30 seconds until fragrant.

Add the sliced onions and bell peppers to the pan. Stir-fry them for 3-4 minutes until they are slightly tender but still crisp.

Now, add the diced tomatoes to the pan with the vegetables. Cook for an additional 2 minutes until the tomatoes are soft and release their juices.

Pour the prepared vegan stir-fry sauce over the vegetables and tomatoes. Toss everything together. Cook for another 1-2 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.

Add the cooked tofu back into the pan with the vegetables and sauce. Stir everything together and cook for another 1-2 minutes to heat the tofu through and coat it with the sauce.

Season the stir-fry with salt and pepper according to your taste.

Serve the spicy vegetable stir-fry over a bed of garlic rice. To make the garlic rice, you can simply mix the cooked rice with a teaspoon of minced garlic and a pinch of salt.

Enjoy your vegan-friendly and flavorful spicy vegetable stir-fry, served with garlic rice cooked on your stove! Feel free to customize the vegetables and spice level to your preference. Happy cooking!

