ChatGPT
Got it! Since you have limited time available and prefer an Indian-inspired dish, let's create a quick and flavorful Indian-style vegan stir-fry using the ingredients and stove you have.

Quick Indian-Style Vegan Stir-Fry:

Ingredients:

1 cup firm tofu, cubed (or substitute with tempeh or chickpeas for protein)
1 red bell pepper, sliced into strips
1 green bell pepper, sliced into strips
1 large onion, thinly sliced
2 tomatoes, diced
4 cloves of garlic, minced
2 cups of cooked basmati rice
3 tablespoons vegetable oil (e.g., olive oil or coconut oil)
1 teaspoon cumin seeds
1 teaspoon ground coriander
1/2 teaspoon ground turmeric
1/2 teaspoon red chili powder (adjust to your preferred spice level)
Salt and pepper to taste
Fresh cilantro leaves for garnish (optional)
Instructions:

Heat 3 tablespoons of vegetable oil in a large skillet or pan over medium-high heat. Add the cumin seeds and allow them to sizzle for a few seconds until aromatic.

Add the minced garlic to the pan and sauté for about 30 seconds until fragrant.

Toss in the cubed tofu (or your preferred vegan protein) and cook until it's lightly browned and slightly crispy, about 4-5 minutes. Remove the tofu from the pan and set aside.

In the same pan, add the sliced onions and bell peppers. Stir-fry them for 3-4 minutes until they are slightly tender but still have a bit of crunch.

Now, add the diced tomatoes to the pan with the vegetables. Cook for an additional 2 minutes until the tomatoes are soft and release their juices.

Reduce the heat to medium-low, and add the ground coriander, ground turmeric, and red chili powder to the pan. Mix everything well to coat the vegetables with the Indian spices.

Return the cooked tofu to the pan and toss it with the spiced vegetables. Let everything cook together for 1-2 minutes to infuse the flavors.

Season the stir-fry with salt and pepper to taste.

Serve the Indian-style vegan stir-fry over a bed of cooked basmati rice. Garnish with fresh cilantro leaves if desired.

Enjoy your quick and flavorful Indian-style vegan stir-fry, served with basmati rice, and prepared on your stove in just 15 minutes! Feel free to adjust the spice level and add any other Indian spices you prefer. Happy cooking and savor your delicious meal!

