Perfect! You're looking for a spicy appetizer that is also quick and flavorful. Let's create a mouthwatering Indian-inspired appetizer using the stove and the available ingredients:

Spicy Indian-Style Tofu Tikka Appetizer:

Ingredients:

1 cup firm tofu, cubed
1 red bell pepper, sliced into strips
1 green bell pepper, sliced into strips
1 large onion, thinly sliced
4 cloves of garlic, minced
2 tablespoons vegetable oil (e.g., olive oil or coconut oil)
1 tablespoon tomato paste or pureed tomatoes
1 tablespoon soy sauce (or tamari for gluten-free)
1 teaspoon ground cumin
1 teaspoon ground coriander
1 teaspoon garam masala
1/2 teaspoon red chili powder (adjust to your preferred spice level)
Salt and pepper to taste
Skewers (wooden or metal)
Instructions:

Preheat your stove on medium-high heat.

In a medium-sized mixing bowl, combine the minced garlic, tomato paste (or pureed tomatoes), soy sauce, ground cumin, ground coriander, garam masala, red chili powder, salt, and pepper to form the marinade.

Add the cubed tofu to the marinade and toss gently to coat the tofu evenly. Let it marinate for about 5 minutes.

While the tofu is marinating, thread the tofu cubes, bell pepper strips, and onion slices onto the skewers alternately.

Heat the vegetable oil in a large skillet or grill pan over medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, place the tofu skewers on the pan and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side until they get slightly charred and golden brown.

Brush any remaining marinade over the skewers while cooking for extra flavor.

Once the tofu and vegetables are cooked to your liking, remove the skewers from the pan.

Serve the spicy Indian-style tofu tikka appetizer hot with a side of your favorite dipping sauce or chutney.

Enjoy your quick and spicy Indian-inspired tofu tikka appetizer, made on your stove! The flavorful blend of spices will surely be a hit with your guests or as a delightful snack for yourself. Happy cooking and enjoy your delicious creation!

